						"description": "⚠️ THIS WILL FAIL - Even with valid Authorization header!\n\nWHY?\n🚧 Layer 1 Security: Network Isolation\n- Port 8002 has NO external port mapping in docker-compose.yml\n- Your computer cannot connect to localhost:8002\n- Connection refused BEFORE token is checked\n- This is intentional security design!\n\n🔑 Layer 2 Security: JWT Authentication\n- Only matters IF you can reach the service\n- From inside Docker network, token IS required\n\n✅ TO TEST THIS SERVICE:\n1. Use: ./test_security.sh (runs inside Docker)\n2. Or exec into container: docker exec -it am-am-user-management-1 sh\n3. Then call: http://am-python-internal-service:8002\n\nThis request demonstrates Layer 1 security working!"
