			"description": "⚠️ EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: These requests will FAIL from Postman!\n\n🔒 TWO-LAYER SECURITY EXPLAINED:\n\n📍 LAYER 1: Network Isolation (Physical Barrier)\n- Port 8002 has NO port mapping in docker-compose.yml\n- Your computer CANNOT connect to localhost:8002\n- Even with valid JWT token, connection is REFUSED\n- This happens BEFORE authentication is checked\n\n🔑 LAYER 2: JWT Authentication (Token Validation)\n- Only matters IF you can reach the service\n- From inside Docker network, valid token IS required\n- Without token from inside: 401 Unauthorized\n- With valid token from inside: 200 OK\n\n💡 WHY THIS DESIGN?\nDefense in Depth:\n- Stolen JWT token? Still can't access from outside ✅\n- Bypass network? Still need valid token ✅\n- Internal services never exposed to internet ✅\n\n✅ TO TEST INTERNAL SERVICES:\n1. Run: ./test_security.sh (8/8 tests passing)\n2. Run: python3 generate_token.py (fresh tokens)\n3. Or exec: docker exec -it am-am-user-management-1 sh\n\n📊 Current Status: All security layers working perfectly!"
		},
